page.title: 06RAILWAYS IN NORTH BRENT
page.content: The train that stops at South Kenton departs from the main line terminal, Euston.It's destination is Watford juntion.The high speed trains which do not stop at South Kenton also departs at Euston.They stop at Watford ,Coventry, Birmingham Inter- national ,Birmingham New Street , Wolverhampton. The Preston Road station is on the Metropolitain line.The main part of the line starts out at Amersham and ends at Barking.The metropolitain stops in our area are Wembley Park, Preston Road and Northwick Park. The Jubilee line was recently built. It starts out at Charing Cross and ends at Stanmore.The stations in our area are Kingsbury and Wembley Park.
